## Vercel Web Analytics Installation Complete

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Compression Analyzer Next.js project.

### Changes Made

**1. Package Installation**
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package (latest version)
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with resolved dependencies

**2. Analytics Integration**
- Modified `app/layout.tsx` to include Vercel Analytics
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the body tag in the root layout

**Files Modified:**
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics import and component
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Lock file updated with new dependencies

### Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), I implemented the Next.js App Router pattern:

1. Imported the Analytics component from `@vercel/analytics/next` (the Next.js-specific export)
2. Placed the component inside the `<body>` tag after the existing content in the root layout
3. This ensures analytics tracking is active across all pages of the application

### Verification Steps Completed

✅ **Build**: Successfully built the project with `npm run build` - no errors
✅ **Linter**: Ran `npm run lint` - passed with no issues
✅ **Tests**: Ran `npm run test` - all 159 tests passed across 15 test files
✅ **Dependencies**: Lock file properly updated with npm install

### Next Steps

Once deployed to Vercel, the analytics will automatically start tracking page views and web vitals. No additional configuration is required. The analytics data will be available in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics tab for this project.

### Notes

- The Analytics component is placed at the end of the body tag to avoid blocking page rendering
- The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation recommendations
- The component works seamlessly with Next.js App Router architecture
- All existing functionality remains intact - this is a purely additive change
